#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/rerender-derived-state-no-effect.md
M|rules|title: Calculate Derived State During Rendering
M|rules|impact: MEDIUM
M|rules|impactDescription: avoids redundant renders and state drift
M|rules|tags: rerender, derived-state, useEffect, state
M|rules|If a value can be computed from current props/state, do not store it in state or update it in an effect. Derive it during render to avoid extra renders and state drift. Do not set state in effects sol
M|rules|**Incorrect (redundant state and effect):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function Form() {
M|rules|const [firstName, setFirstName] = useState('First')
M|rules|const [lastName, setLastName] = useState('Last')
M|rules|const [fullName, setFullName] = useState('')
M|rules|useEffect(() => {
M|rules|setFullName(firstName + ' ' + lastName)
M|rules|}, [firstName, lastName])
M|rules|return <p>{fullName}</p>
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (derive during render):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|function Form() {
M|rules|const [firstName, setFirstName] = useState('First')
M|rules|const [lastName, setLastName] = useState('Last')
M|rules|const fullName = firstName + ' ' + lastName
M|rules|return <p>{fullName}</p>
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|References: [You Might Not Need an Effect](https://react.dev/learn/you-might-not-need-an-effect)